{"sequence":54,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T22:14:18.806538706Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-83357f95","body":"finding_summary: Missing plan hashes are treated as \"current plan\", so historical milestone tasks/runs with unknown provenance can be relabeled with today's bead title and acceptance criteria.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2141-2169\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2224-2233\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2298-2313\n- src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:1379-1388\nremediation_hint: Only project plan-derived fields when every referenced task/run carries an explicit plan hash that matches the current plan; if any hash is missing or mixed, fall back to milestone/bead IDs with bead_title/acceptance_criteria omitted.","dedup_key":"e649ac5dcfa287694b52fd8f4820248ca272c096b3f9b88199c38a750e28619a","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":55,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T22:14:18.815146612Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-69be8272","body":"finding_summary: The new lineage readers trust any JSON-shaped `plan.json`; they do not verify `bundle.identity.id` or run bundle validation, so a parseable but wrong/corrupt plan can feed bogus bead titles and acceptance criteria into task detail and milestone queries.\nseverity: low\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2065-2077\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2182-2188\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2285-2306\nremediation_hint: Reuse the validated loader pattern already used in `src/cli/project.rs:812-840` (identity check, legacy backfill, `bundle.validate()`), and treat any validation failure like the existing missing/corrupt-plan path so the query degrades to fallback lineage instead of returning potentially incorrect metadata.","dedup_key":"102fc7f234ec589dd6ec14228129922d53324ed928f82da911deca20ffaba533","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":56,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T22:14:18.823778873Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-2301878d","body":"finding_summary: Bead execution history still filters task-run lineage rows with raw string equality, so `bead_execution_history(\"bead-1\")` and `bead_execution_history(\"ms-alpha.bead-1\")` are not equivalent even though milestone bead refs are canonicalized elsewhere.\nseverity: medium\naffected_files:\n- src/adapters/fs.rs:5161-5171\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2206-2224\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bead_refs.rs:3-15\nremediation_hint: Canonicalize the requested bead ref and stored row ids (or compare via `milestone_bead_refs_match`) before filtering, and add a test that mixes short and fully qualified bead IDs.","dedup_key":"a33c634f4542966435fc55b4cc1f57cef3b0f745a3e370e83948c53b9dd5354c","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
