{"sequence":73,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T22:42:47.129604444Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-63ec00b8","body":"finding_summary: `bead_execution_history` can report one execution attempt twice when the underlying start/completion rows use short vs fully-qualified bead IDs. severity: medium. affected_files: [\"src/adapters/fs.rs\", \"src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs\"]. evidence: the new query path filters rows with `milestone_bead_refs_match` in `FsTaskRunLineageStore::find_runs_for_bead` (`src/adapters/fs.rs:5168-5172`), but attempt collapsing still keys on raw `bead_id` equality because `TaskRunEntry::same_attempt` requires `left.bead_id == right.bead_id` (`src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:393-405`) and `collapse_task_run_attempts` relies on that matcher (`src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs:611-698`). If a running row was written as `bead-1` and the terminal replay/repair row was written as `ms-alpha.bead-1` for the same `project_id`/`run_id`, collapse leaves two entries and the new filter returns both, so retries/history become incorrect. remediation_hint: canonicalize bead refs before grouping, or make the collapse/matching helpers use milestone-aware bead comparison consistently.","dedup_key":"77d15c35e6b785231dcc213de20a2628a682eb871243b342774563376b6e5ce9","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":74,"timestamp":"2026-04-15T22:42:47.139510225Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-e2a3f015","body":"finding_summary: task detail lookups now silently hide lineage whenever milestone lookup fails, so a broken bead-backed task becomes indistinguishable from a standalone project/task. severity: medium. affected_files: [\"src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs\", \"src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs\"]. evidence: `load_task_lineage_detail` converts every `read_bead_lineage` error into `Ok(None)` at `src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs:1379-1389`. But `read_bead_lineage` already downgrades missing/corrupt `plan.json` into a fallback lineage internally (`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:2230-2241`), so the remaining errors are real failures such as a missing/unreadable milestone record. In those cases `project show` / `task show` now succeed with no lineage at all, which defeats the new feature and masks on-disk corruption. remediation_hint: keep the internal plan fallback, but propagate hard milestone-store errors (or return an explicit degraded lineage state) instead of collapsing them to `None`.","dedup_key":"ac93712626f7b60266c0d2366173c824ba992da3ceaa4914491a13d2f6162154","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260415203322","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
